What is the process like from getting from the airport directly to the cruise ships using the shuttle services or taxis? Once you arrive to the port is it pretty easy to get to your ship with your luggage etc?
Written October 27, 2019
KenS92
Braintree, United Kingdom
95 contributions
Easiest way is to take a taxi from the airport to cruise port. Its about 20km - takes about half hour and costs around €35. Taxi will drop you at the appropriate terminal building where your particular ship is berthed. Porters will take your luggage from your taxi and load onto trolley to go on ship - make sure your bags are tagged with your stateroom number. All you need to do is show your cruise ticket documents to enter in the terminal building and join a line for check in. Hope this helps. Have a great cruise.
